<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <%- include('templates/main/head', {title}) %>
</head>

<body>

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <div>
        <%- include('templates/main/navbar', {title}) %>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="page-header">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>About Us</h1>
            <p>Learn more about JP Alorwu and the website designed for book lovers.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- About the Author Section -->
    <section class="about-section about-author">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row align-items-center">
                <!-- Author Image -->
                <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
                    <img src="/images/JP_alorwu_trans.png" alt="JP Alorwu" class="img-fluid mb-4">
                </div>
                <!-- Author Bio -->
                <div class="col-md-8">
                    <h2>About the Author</h2>
                    <p>
                        Ms. Justine Perfect Alorwu is an author, a passionate, dedicated and certified personal
                        development coach committed to guiding teenagers and young adults discover their life’s true
                        purpose and kick start their journey to early success in their personal, academic and future
                        professional lives.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        With over five years of experience in the field, Ms. Alorwu continues to visit junior and senior
                        high schools including special schools, to help countless students unlock their full potential,
                        empower them to overcome their obstacles, set and achieve meaningful goals, and cultivate a
                        mindset of success while living their best lives.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Ms. Alorwu holds a Bachelor’s Degree in Social Work from the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science
                        and Technology, Kumasi Ghana. She is currently studying for a Master of Science in International
                        Relations at the Accra Business School in Ghana.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- About the Website Section -->
    <section class="about-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="text-center">About the Website</h2>
            <p>This website is a one-stop platform for buying, reading, and exploring JP Alorwu's books online. Designed
                with the modern reader in mind, the website provides an easy-to-use interface where you can browse
                through an extensive collection of books, purchase them securely, and even leave reviews for other
                readers.</p>
            <p>We aim to create a seamless experience for book lovers. Whether you're looking for a heartwarming romance
                or a thrilling mystery, JP Alorwu's website has something for everyone. You can also explore exclusive
                content, get insights into the author's creative process, and stay updated on the latest releases.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="footer">
        <%- include('templates/main/footer') %>
    </footer>

    <%- include('templates/main/baseScripts') %>
        <!-- <script-- type="text/javascript" src="../backend/public/js/bookList.js"></script-->
        <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/mainFuncs.js"></script>
        <!-- <script type="text/javascript" src="../backend/public/js/templatemo.custom.js"></script> -->

</body>

</html>